items.term: An investigation method used to detect unilateral hypofunction of the peripheral vestibular system caused mainly by acute vestibulopathy. The performer of the test sits face to face with the patient and holding the patient's head from the front. The patient is advised to fix their gaze on a target and the head is rapidly turned to one side and then to the other side while watching the eyes for the presence or absence of any corrective movements.
